detaileddescription.para: The RoutineStatus parameter identifies the current status of a routine, a sub-program or a function at the time of a results query (RoutineControlType=0x03) The ICAS1 shall send the RoutineInfo parameter (1Byte) containing following parameters in the Positive Response to a RequestRoutineResults request: Bits 0 to 3: RoutineStatus
Routine control result - part of RoutineInfo byte Bits 4 to 7: RoutineResult This parameter is used to describe if the routine has generated results, and if they are correct or not.
